                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Haldeman</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">[Extract.]</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 19, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * </p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * </p>
                <p>The information which you give concerning the temper and feeling of the
                    government and people of Sweden is very gratifying.</p>
                <p>This government will find a sincere pleasure in doing all that shall be in its
                    power to favor the safety and freedom of the commerce of Sweden in the ports of
                    the United States not closed by the blockade.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jacob S. Haldeman</hi>, Esq.,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Stockholm</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
